race.comment: JUST LEGENDARY (5) resumes for the top local barn and has been transferred from a leading Sydney stable. He led just beaten at Gosford two starts back on debut and that's good form for this. He's trialled well with today's rider Newman aboard. He can jump and run from an inside gate and should be naturally improved. FLORAL LEGEND (8) also switched from a Sydney barn and didn't finish it off at the Sunshine Coast when expected to win. She brought strong relative form to that and should be better for the run. Tackles 1200m for the first time but she will use the inside gate in easier grade and can make amends. SHREDDED (6) is a stablemate to the top selection and he has also switched from a Sydney barn. He was last seen placing at Goulburn 157 days ago and has trialled well. As with the pair above, the betting will be key. CAUTIONARY TAIL (4) debuts with Lloyd booked and showed enough in his latest trial to keep onside.
